DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: To organize and oversee.:A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn._A research study that prospectively assigns human participants or groups of humans to one or more health-related interventions to evaluate the effects on health outcomes. Interventions include but are not restricted to drugs, cells and other biological products, surgical procedures, radiologic procedures, devices, behavioral treatments, process-of-care changes, and preventive care.
